<servinfosub id = "AENCP70AA804003002">
<title>
Diagnosis Procedure
</title>
<attention3>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Be sure to perform 
<intxref refid = "AENCP70AA804001">CAN Communication Check</intxref>
 before perform this flow.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Occurrence of multiple troubles is not included in the scope of this trouble diagnosis.
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</attention3>
<ptxt>
When “Lost Communication” is detected in any control module, perform diagnosing according to the following procedure.
</ptxt>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Connect SUZUKI scan tool to DLC.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Set ignition “ON”.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Select “Communication Bus Check” under “Bus Check” menu of SUZUKI scan tool and check for disabled communicating control module (it is not displayed on screen).
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Based on above check results, select applicable diagnosis flow ([a] to [k]) from 
<intxref refid = "AENCP70AA804003003">Diagnosis Flow Selection Table</intxref>
.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Perform troubleshooting according to selected diagnosis flow.
</ptxt>
</s1>
</servinfosub>
<servinfosub id = "AENCP70AA804003003">
<title>
Diagnosis Flow Selection Table
</title>
<attention3>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Check if the contact condition at connectors including power supply and ground circuits is in good condition, before performing this diagnosis.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
If it is not possible to select suitable diagnosis flow from “Diagnosis Flow Selection Table” or “two or more diagnosis flows are selectable”, perform 
<intxref refid = "AENCP70AA804004">Troubleshooting for Communication Bus Off</intxref>
.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Diagnosis flows [a] to [k] link with CAN communication lines [a] to [k] of 
<intxref refid = "AENCP70AA804003001">Circuit Diagram</intxref>
.
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</attention3>
